 Native American Archery Equipment Charles Acua is widely considered to be the finest artisan of native American archery equipment working today. The bows shown are both of osage orange, the traditional bow wood of the Apache and other Southwestern Tribes. Charlie uses the Traditional Bowyer's Bible as his basic reference work. Volume Two Volume Three Stone Edge Home Page . Ketoh (Navajo bracer) on George's page. This site designed and maintained by Arco Iris Web Designs, LLC . Copyright 1998. 
